(518, 1, '2020-11-02 12:53:03', '2020-11-02 12:53:03', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1603958313435{background-image: url(http://angur.local.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/kitchen_corner.gif?id=467) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\" el_class=\"Main_Page_Banner Recipe_Main_Page_Banner\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner el_class=\"page_name_container about_page_name_container\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"recipe_container\"][vc_custom_heading text=\"Recipe\" font_container=\"tag:h1|text_align:center\" css_animation=\"fadeInUp\" el_class=\"page_name\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"fadeInUp\" el_class=\"page_name_para\"]\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Latest Tasty Recipes</p>\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"container recipe-section-main\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"541\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Dal Fry[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]An Indian can never have enough of dals. And I hope you guys aren’t bored with my dal recipes because they will be here all the time. No escaping!\n\nEasy Dal Fry which goes so well with boiled rice or tandoori roti.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"/dal-fry\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section left-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Dal Makhani[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]Creamy and buttery Dal Makhani is one of India’s most loved dal!\n\nThis dal has whole black lentils cooked with butter and cream and simmered on 