(533, 1, '2020-10-30 12:01:41', '2020-10-30 12:01:41', '[vc_row css=\".vc_custom_1603958313435{background-image: url(http://angur.local.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/10/kitchen_corner.gif?id=467) !important;background-position: center !important;background-repeat: no-repeat !important;background-size: cover !important;}\" el_class=\"Main_Page_Banner Recipe_Main_Page_Banner\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner el_class=\"page_name_container\"][vc_column_inner][vc_custom_heading text=\"Recipe\" font_container=\"tag:h1|text_align:center\" css_animation=\"fadeInUp\" el_class=\"page_name\"][vc_column_text css_animation=\"fadeInUp\" el_class=\"page_name_para\"]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Latest Tasty Recipes</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"container recipe-section-main\"][vc_column][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"215\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Dal Fry[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]An Indian can never have enough of dals. And I hope you guys aren’t bored with my dal recipes because they will be here all the time. No escaping!\r\n\r\nEasy Dal Fry which goes so well with boiled rice or tandoori roti.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"#\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section left-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Dal Makhani[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]Creamy and buttery Dal Makhani is one of India’s most loved dal!\r\n\r\nThis dal has whole black lentils cooked with butter and cream and simmered on low heat for that unique flavor. It tastes best with garlic naan![/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"#\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section right-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"223\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"215\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Instant Pot Kale Garlic Dal[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]Instant Pot Kale Garlic Dal – this dal has robust flavors from lots of garlic and packs a healthy punch! It’s vegan and super easy to make using the frozen onion tomato masala that I shared on the blog earlier this week.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"#\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section left-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Butternut Squash Dal[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]And another easy recipe for a vegetarian Thanksgiving to end the week! This Butternut Squash Dal combines lentils with onion, tomato and is lightly tempered with mustard, cumin and curry leaves. Serve it with naan or rice! Vegan and gluten-free.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"#\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section right-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"223\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '', '2020-10-30 12:01:41', '2020-10-30 12:01:41', '', 210, 'http://angur.local.com/210-revis