vor. It tastes best with garlic naan![/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"/dal-makhani\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section right-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"597\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"543\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Instant Pot Kale Garlic Dal[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]Instant Pot Kale Garlic Dal – this dal has robust flavors from lots of garlic and packs a healthy punch! It’s vegan and super easy to make using the frozen onion tomato masala that I shared on the blog earlier this week.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"/instant-pot-kale-garlic-dal\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner el_class=\"recipe-main-blog\"][vc_column_inner el_class=\"right-des-section left-des-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-title\"]Butternut Squash Dal[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"recipe-description\"]And another easy recipe for a vegetarian Thanksgiving to end the week! This Butternut Squash Dal combines lentils with onion, tomato and is lightly tempered with mustard, cumin and curry leaves. Serve it with naan or rice! Vegan and gluten-free.[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"learn-more-btn\"]<a href=\"/butternut-squash-dal\"> Learn More </a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"left-img-section right-img-section\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_single_image image=\"544\" img_size=\"full\"][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>\r\n', 'Recipe', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '210-revision-v1', '', '',